Labour leader Ed Miliband said he would not do a deal with the SNP to become Prime Minister . 
  But Nicola Sturgeon said he will 'change his tune' after the election . 
  She said he simply 'won't have the votes to do what he likes come what may' She called on Labour to 'work together to lock the Tories out' of Downing Street . 
  Polls show the SNP is on course for a landslide victory in the General Election . 
  Mr Miliband today told BBC1's Andrew Marr Show he would 'not do any deals with SNP'